-- Colombian Stocks: Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp., Canacol Energy
-- B y   C h r i s t i n e   J e n k i n s
-- 2012-03-29T21:14:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-29/colombian-stocks-pacific-rubiales-energy-corp-canacol-energy.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close of trading.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  gained 0.9 percent to 15,154.97. A 20
percent increase so far this year would be the biggest quarterly
advance since the three months through June 2009.  The Colcap Index gained 0.8 percent to 1,751.47.  Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp. (PREC)  , the Toronto-based
oil producer that operates fields in Colombia, rose 1.4 percent
to 52,340 pesos. Pacific Rubiales will invest as much as $140
million in Pacific Infrastructure Inc., a company developing an
oil port and pipeline, the company said in a statement.  Canacol Energy Ltd. (CNEC)  , the Calgary-based  oil
company  that operates fields in Colombia, fell 1.5 percent to
1,620 pesos. Oil declined to the lowest level in six weeks in
 New York .  To contact the reporter on this story:
